doi_primary.notes: Valid PhysioNet DOI format for dataset version 1.1

version_consistency.notes: All version references align with v1.1 as the evaluated version. Latest version 2.0.1 properly documented.

dataset_purpose.primary_goal: Create ethically sourced voice biomarker dataset for AI research

data_composition.notes: Clear hierarchical structure with 4 distinct data subsets

privacy_protection_strategy.notes: Layered privacy approach: de-identification + data minimization + access control

missing_fields: version (no explicit version field, only in updates)
doi (no separate doi field, DOI used as id)
software_and_tools (tools mentioned in preprocessing but not in dedicated field)

strengths: Strong persistent identifier (DOI as primary ID)
Comprehensive description of dataset purpose and composition
Excellent privacy documentation (HIPAA Safe Harbor + layered protections)
Clear IRB approval and informed consent documentation
Detailed preprocessing and feature extraction pipeline
Well-documented versioning with multiple versions tracked
Clear access control and licensing requirements
Multiple data subsets with technical specifications
weaknesses: No variable-level metadata for phenotype and feature files
Missing dataset limitations and known biases
No prohibited or intended uses (only discouraged uses)
No software tools formally listed (mentioned in preprocessing)
No external resources or related datasets
No compensation or vulnerable population details
